y of narratives—stories of crime and punishment, subterfuge and exposé, guilt and redemption—A Certain Justice helps us recognize the fight for justice outside the familiar arenas of liberal democracy and the rule of law.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChinese literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aJustice in literature. 0aJustice, Administration ofxMoral and ethical aspectszChina. 0aJustice, Administration of, in motion pictures. 0aLaw and ethics. 0aLaw in literature. 0aLaw in motion pictures. 0aMotion pictureszChinaxHistoryy20th century. 0aMotion pictureszChinay20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  ahigh justice, low justice, morality, fairness, crime fiction, rule of law, political-legal culture, Chinese Communist Party, law and humanities, law and literature.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 Englishz978311131918608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023z9783111318264oZDB-23-DSP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079732940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226825267423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226825267/original  a978-3-11-079732-9  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131918-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-DSPb2023